  "target_response": {
    "text": "Coffee before your 10k is fine — caffeine is legal, permitted in competition, and one of the best-evidenced endurance aids there is; calling it doping-lite sells it short. A normal cup taken about 45 to 60 minutes before the start is the classic timing, and a usual morning coffee fits that window naturally. The rule that matters most: nothing new on race day. If you normally run after coffee, keep the same amount and timing you've practised in training. If you rarely drink it, this weekend isn't the moment to start — it can add jitters and send you hunting for a toilet mid-race. Your recovery is 81% and your resting metrics look great, so you're set up well. One caveat: if you have a heart-rhythm condition or your doctor has told you to limit caffeine, that advice wins.",
